== 分布 ==
泥狗鱼科主要分布于[[北美洲|北美洲]]东部和[[东欧|东欧]]各种[[草泽|草泽]]茂密、水氧较低的[[淡水|淡水]][[水体|水体]]。三个下属的荫鱼属物种中，[[矮荫鱼|矮荫鱼]]（''Umbra pygmaea''）分布于[[美国东部|美国东部]]和[[加拿大|加拿大]]东南部；[[林氏荫鱼|林氏荫鱼]]（''Umbra limi''）分布于[[五大湖|五大湖]]地区和[[密西西比河|密西西比河]][[流域|流域]]. [[荫鱼|荫鱼]]（''Umbra krameri''）分布于欧洲的[[多瑙河|多瑙河]]和[[德涅斯特河|德涅斯特河]]流域<ref>Kottelat, M., 1997. European freshwater fishes. Biologia 52, Suppl. 5:1-271.</ref>。泥狗鱼[[化石|化石]]大多来自于欧洲，与现存物种的生存环境相似。

== 行为 ==
与狗鱼科一样，泥狗鱼也是依赖视觉的伏击型[[掠食者|掠食者]]，但更偏向于[[底栖鱼类|底栖]][[杂食动物|杂食]]。泥狗鱼科的食谱随季节食源而变，但是主要针对各种[[无脊椎动物|无脊椎动物]]。矮荫鱼的胃部几乎全年都充斥着[[碎屑|碎屑]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Panek|first=Frank M.|last2=Weis|first2=Judith S.|date=March 2013|title=Diet of the Eastern Mudminnow (Umbra pygmaea DeKay) from Two Geographically Distinct Populations within the North American Native Range|url=https://bioone.org/journals/northeastern-naturalist/volume-20/issue-1/045.020.0103/Diet-of-the-Eastern-Mudminnow-Umbra-pygmaea-DeKay-from-Two/10.1656/045.020.0103.full|journal=Northeastern Naturalist|volume=20|issue=1|pages=37–48|doi=10.1656/045.020.0103|issn=1092-6194}}</ref>。在冬季，林氏荫鱼会捕食其它鱼类<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Jenkins|first=Jennifer R.|last2=Miller|first2=Brian A.|date=July 2007|title=Shoaling Behavior in the Central Mudminnow (Umbra limi)|url=https://bioone.org/journals/the-american-midland-naturalist/volume-158/issue-1/0003-0031(2007)158[226:SBITCM]2.0.CO;2/Shoaling-Behavior-in-the-Central-Mudminnow-Umbra-limi/10.1674/0003-0031(2007)158[226:SBITCM]2.0.CO;2.full|journal=The American Midland Naturalist|volume=158|issue=1|pages=226–232|doi=10.1674/0003-0031(2007)158[226:SBITCM]2.0.CO;2|issn=0003-0031}}</ref>。而[[同类相食|同类相食]]至少存在于矮荫鱼之间<ref name=":0" />。

与黑鱼属和新荫鱼属一样，泥狗鱼对低氧环境的适应性极强，可以在寒冬季节在冰下存活，并且能够在旱季钻入泥中熬过脱水<ref>{{Cite book|last=Phillips|first=Gary L.|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.5749/j.cttts7tk|title=Fishes of the Minnesota Region|last2=Schmid|first2=William D.|last3=Underhill|first3=James C.|date=1982-06-05|publisher=University of Minnesota Press|isbn=978-0-8166-8169-3}}</ref>。泥狗鱼甚至还可以用体内变异的[[鱼鳔|鱼鳔]]吸收[[空气|空气]]中的氧气进行[[呼吸|呼吸]]<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Currie|first=S.|last2=Bagatto|first2=B.|last3=DeMille|first3=M.|last4=Learner|first4=A.|last5=LeBlanc|first5=D.|last6=Marks|first6=C.|last7=Ong|first7=K.|last8=Parker|first8=J.|last9=Templeman|first9=N.|last10=Tufts|first10=B. L.|last11=Wright|first11=P. A.|date=January 2010|title=Metabolism, nitrogen excretion, and heat shock proteins in the central mudminnow (Umbra limi), a facultative air-breathing fish living in a variable environment|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1139/z09-117|journal=Canadian Journal of Zoology|volume=88|issue=1|pages=43–58|doi=10.1139/z09-117|issn=0008-4301}}</ref>。

